                  </persName>
            , and 
               <persName id="t17340424-5-person58">
                  Edward 
                  Ayre 
               <interp inst="t17340424-5-person58" type="surname" value="Ayre"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17340424-5-person58" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17340424-5-person58" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of a parcel of Linnen, value 21 l. under pretence of being a Shop-keeper at Brentford; and that if they sent the Goods by a Servant, he wou'd pay the Money upon the Delivery.</p>
               <p>But the Prisoner being Capitally convicted on the former indictment, he was not try'd on this.</p>
